{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015UPZuf1yukprnebS5o42QH","type":"tool_result","content":"# ray/dashboard_exposure\n# Expose Ray dashboard on port 8265 via the ray-head Service\n\nprompt: |\n  The Ray dashboard should be reachable from inside the cluster, but the\n  ray-head Service only exposes the GCS port.\n\n  Your task: update the ray-head Service to expose the dashboard on port {{params.dashboard_port}}.\n\n  Use this command to test:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray exec curl-test -- curl -sS -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" \\\n    http://ray-head:{{params.dashboard_port}}/api/cluster_status\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: the command returns HTTP 200.\n\nparams:\n  dashboard_port:\n    default: 8265\n    description: Port on the ray-head Service that exposes the Ray dashboard\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/curl-test.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/curl-test --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\n  # Additive fixture unit (Rule 4): the oracle's HTTP check execs into the\n  # curl-test pod. Standalone, ray_env_ready's apply creates it. But in a\n  # workflow where this case inherits a live cluster from a prior stage (deploy\n  # /scale), ray_env_ready's apply is skipped and no prior case creates\n  # curl-test, so the oracle would fail with no test pod. This unit ensures JUST\n  # the curl-test pod idempotently, gated by its own probe, WITHOUT touching the\n  # cluster/namespace. Standalone it is a harmless no-op (the pod already exists).\n  - name: curl_test_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test 2>/dev/null | grep -c curl-test\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/curl-test.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/curl-test --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test 2>/dev/null | grep -c curl-test\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 180","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c2931229-dbec-46ca-85c4-3c38f5d077be","uuid":"d66a5767-3ddc-4324-a1da-c5c023be5572","timestamp":"2026-06-23T15:54:07.343Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# ray/dashboard_exposure\n# Expose Ray dashboard on port 8265 via the ray-head Service\n\nprompt: |\n  The Ray dashboard should be reachable from inside the cluster, but the\n  ray-head Service only exposes the GCS port.\n\n  Your task: update the ray-head Service to expose the dashboard on port {{params.dashboard_port}}.\n\n  Use this command to test:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray exec curl-test -- curl -sS -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" \\\n    http://ray-head:{{params.dashboard_port}}/api/cluster_status\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: the command returns HTTP 200.\n\nparams:\n  dashboard_port:\n    default: 8265\n    description: Port on the ray-head Service that exposes the Ray dashboard\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/curl-test.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/curl-test --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\n  # Additive fixture unit (Rule 4): the oracle's HTTP check execs into the\n  # curl-test pod. Standalone, ray_env_ready's apply creates it. But in a\n  # workflow where this case inherits a live cluster from a prior stage (deploy\n  # /scale), ray_env_ready's apply is skipped and no prior case creates\n  # curl-test, so the oracle would fail with no test pod. This unit ensures JUST\n  # the curl-test pod idempotently, gated by its own probe, WITHOUT touching the\n  # cluster/namespace. Standalone it is a harmless no-op (the pod already exists).\n  - name: curl_test_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test 2>/dev/null | grep -c curl-test\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/curl-test.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/curl-test --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test 2>/dev/null | grep -c curl-test\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 180","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
